<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2347> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2347" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 38.60.3, from Val. Ant. He spoke for the majority of the Tribunes in refusing Scipio Nasica's appeal to them to veto the execution of Terentius Culleo's judgment against L. Scipio.{376}" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2346> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2346" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He is mentioned only in Antias' version which dates him in 187. But his connection with the execution of judgment against L. Scipio and with Ti.{378} Gracchus who vetoed Scipio's imprisonment justifies the transfer of his name to the time when these trails probably occurred. See 187, on the Petillii and below on Q. Naevius and Ti. Gracchus." .
